    public class RightPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    In RightPanel are displayed all the options concerning log file analysis, using two file chooser, a combo box and two button.
    The first file chooser allows you to select a .csv file in which are stored data from a previous run of the rotor.
    The second file chooser allows you to choose a .properties file in which are located eventual parameter for the analyzer. This file is not compulsory, since a well done GUI will ask you for these parameters if no .properties file is selected.
    The combo box lets you select the analyzer implementation that will analyze data stored in the file.
    The button OPEN starts the file analysis.
    The button VIEW GRAPH draws graphs of the previous run of the rotor represented by the file.

    • Constructor Detail

      • RightPanel

        public RightPanel(Controller cont)
        Creates two file chooser to choose data file and properties file (with filter for .csv and .properties file respectively), populates a Analyzers combo box using AnalyzersFactory.getAnalyzersList() and create the two buttons for launch analysis and view graphs.
        The button OPEN triggers the creation of the selected implementation of an Analyzer using AnalyzersFactory.newInstanceOf(Class, File, File) and passing the selected files, and launch another specifically frame (see Controller.startAnalysis(Analyzer) for displaying results and interacting with the user.
        The button VIEW GRAPH trigger the displaying of another frame (eg. GraphsFrame) to display the graphs recreated basing on the data file.
        Parameters:
        cont - the controller that allows to perform the operations such as starting the analysis.
